{How to finish the development?} 9. Nh3 $1 {Well-known idea which is quite
typical for Samisch Variation of KID. Whenever Black develops his knight to d7
closing the way of the light-squared bishop, White gets the option of
developing his knight to h3. The knight is heading for the perfect f2-square.
From this position, he protects the e4-pawn and takes under control the
important g4-square.} e6 {then what?} 10. dxe6 $1 fxe6 11. Bf3 {White's space
advantage promises him a nice edge here.} *

