{How White should react after 9...h6} 9. Ne1 $1 {a powerful idea, which seems
to promise White a pleasant pull. It appears that White can easily handle this
position without committing for d4-d5-advance. If Black stays passive, White
can follow with simple moves like Nc2, f2-f3, and Qd2 followed by Rac1 and
Rfd1.} Ng4 {Being in a passive position, Black tries to exchange some minor
pieces. Nevertheless, White is usually happy to part with his passive
light-squared bishop.} 10. Bxg4 $1 Bxg4 11. f3 $14 *

